  "doc_id": "28921",
  "text": "To further confirm that NET plays a role in the early inflammatory responses to Sev infection, we administered Cl-amidine, a pan PAD inhibitor with preferential irreversible inactivation of the calcium bound form of PAD4 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] to Sev-infected mice. PAD4 catalyzes the conversion of specific arginine residues to citrulline [CITATION_3] and is essential for the formation of NETs via PAD4-mediated citrullination of histones (18). Cl-amidine suppressed neutrophil accumulation and inflammatory cytokine release in the alveolar space ( Figure 5) . Combined with the DNase 1 treatment results, these findings further confirmed the involvement of NETs in early host responses to Sev.",
